  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\n`eth2_hashing` crate uses `cpufeatures` as a mandatory dependency. `cpufeatures` has a [restriction](https://github.com/RustCrypto/utils/blob/846ae596590941ee87844b54cff8bfbaf3f6bc42/cpufeatures/src/lib.rs#L70) saying `\"This crate works only on `aarch64`, `x86`, and `x86-64` targets.\"`. Because of that, it will not allow compiling this crate to `wasm32` target-arch.\r\n\r\nBasically, `eth2_hashing` crate uses `cpufeatures` only for `detecting the availability for SHA extensions on x86_64` [source](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/564d7da656803f5e06e53a303972580be54500bf/crypto/eth2_hashing/src/lib.rs#L127).\r\nThis actually means that this dependency could be optional.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nRust version: 1.62.0\r\nLighthouse version: `stable` branch, v.2.3.1 at 564d7da\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\n`cpufeatures` dependency is mandatory.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\n`cpufeatures` dependency is optional and available as a feature.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\n* add `cpufeatures` feature;\r\n* make `cpufeature` default feature to preserve the compatibility;\r\n* hide all `cpufeature`-related code with `cpufeatures` feature.\r\n",
